stylometry: A genetic algorithm is a tool that gathers information and gives us answers based on the contraints of the problem.  It allows us to optimize the problem by either maximizing or miniminzing the problem in order to receive the answer we want.  It is helpful to bring data together and have the computer solve the information for us, because if we did not have this capability it would be very hard for a person to obtain this information doing it on their own.  Evolutionary solver is helping and important in solving non-linear model problems because of the amount of data we can enter into the system.  FOr instance in the example of city clusters in the book we had to evolutionary solver because we had a 49 different cities with the percentages of different ethnic groups.  Regular solver would not have been able to solve this problem because of the high amount of cities with their own ethnic groups.
